overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, providing a detailed specification. The assistant performed an
  in-depth analysis of the codebase against the requirements, identifying
  several areas needing improvement. A structured plan was then created,
  prioritizing the identified gaps. The first action item, implementing a 1-10
  tiredness severity scale, was successfully completed. This involved updating
  the data model, validation, and UI components to capture the severity of
  tiredness interference. Crucially, a safety warning was integrated into the
  questionnaire flow and the generated reports for high severity scores,
  advising users to seek immediate professional help and avoid dangerous
  activities. The assistant is now moving on to the next task in the plan.
